    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A print shop sells posters in two sizes. The posters are all printed on the same type of paper, which costs 2 cents per square inch. The shop wants to calculate and display the material cost for each poster. To make future updates easier, they want to define this cost as a constant.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">PrintShop.java</code>, declare and initialize a constant called <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">COST\\_PER\\_SQ\\_INCH</code> to <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">0.02</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getPosterCosts()</code> method, update each line to use the constant instead of the number <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">0.02</code>.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with declaring and initializing a constant.\r\n</div>\r\n",
